message: TWO people have voted for it so far...

i can never get into that one :(

I've tried, but it's confusing as fuck to me.
I might be spoiled by the modern linear and easy games, but i have absolutely no idea what to do after the first 15 minutes.
I havent figured out how to get to the first dungeon.
Right here mate!

Agreed. I would have to say that my favourite is PH, and that LTTP is the best, but Minish Cap was by far the most *enjoyable* to play. Something about that childish feel -- little guys doing big things, with a freaking hilarious talking hat!
Yeah, when you're first discovering all the hidden secrets and stuff. PH will always hold that space in my heart container <3

No, I disagree. It was designed for a little weaker hardware and for a much younger target audience. It fixed a lot of the technical issues of PH while being fun to play. It was quite weak on the actual storytelling, and Malladus was excruciatingly difficult for a young player, but the locomotion and panflute were well executed in regards to the overall feel of the game. 

6/10, might do an easy 3 heart challenge.
Of course.

I've figured out that much, and even managed to get the bomb mask and the fairy mask. I played up to the deku/monkeys (it's been a while, I don't remember what they were) in the swamp, but I wasn not able to talk to any of the NPCs, so I think I'm doing things incorrectly.
I'm only 22 and I feel the same way.
